<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-12-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="634" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d634">
                        <head>No. 634.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Farman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-12-05"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 5,
                                1879</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 147.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The dispatch of Mr. Comanos, numbered 340,
                            of the 8th of October last, respecting the proposed decree for insuring
                            the validity of the mortgage of certain lauds to the Messrs, Rothschild,
                            has been received. In reply to his request for instructions, I have to
                            inform you that a telegram upon the subject was sent on the 11th of
                            October last, the text of .which is as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Comanos</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Vice-Consul, Cairo, Egypt:</hi></p>
                                <p>This government makes no objection to the proposed decree
                                    respecting the domanial loan.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>